user.biography:
Multi-award winning, Scandi inspired Nursery & Kids Boutique. As seen in @britishvogue @archdigest and @telegraph 
UK 🇬🇧 US 🇺🇸 EU 🇪🇺Stores.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Scandi Nursery Decor & Toys in London, United Kingdom with @buildingthemushroom. May be an image of indoor.

node.text:
It’s a wild world out there…

Who’s expecting a baby in the next few months? Have you finished your nursery or still on the hunt for inspo? We can’t stop swooning over this wild space, featuring our Lorena Canals globe bean bag. Search “globe” on the website to shop, or head to stories for a link 🔗

📷 thank you to the lovely @buildingthemushroom

node.text:
🍂 A U T U M N 🍂

Summer packed up earlier than we expected, so let’s skip to the good bit! What’s your favourite part of autumn?? Is it spooky season, long walks, baking, crafts, leaf collecting or maybe duvet days with hot chocolate?? 

In the coming weeks we’ll have lots of A/W inspo for you! And in the meantime, make sure you check out our top autumn picks by shopping this post 🍂

#autumn #fall #halloween #halloweenparty #halloweencostume #autumnwalk #liewoodkids #liewood #olliella #merimeri #partyfood #halloweenpartyfood #duvetday #cosy #schoolholidays #family #love #scandikids #reels #happyautumn #happyhalloween #boo #harvest #pumpkinspice #falldecor #familywalk #autumndecor #kidscrafts #pumpkin #spookyseason

node.text:
🪐 BEFORE & AFTER 🪐

Who loves a transformation?? This one sees a dusty panda palace morph in to a cosy modern take on space theme! What’s your favourite part? 

You can TAP to shop the look or head to the store & browse our space collection 🚀

node.text:
Easy Pizza Pinwheels

Need some packed lunch inspo? Or maybe your little ones are heading home ravenous & need a fun tasty snack? These puff pastry pinwheels & twists are also great for weaning babes!

What would you put in yours? Our favourites are chicken & halloumi! 

INGREDIENTS

🥐  ready roll puff pastry
🥫 sauce
🫑 toppings
🧀 cheese
🥚 egg or milk for wash 

HOW TO

1. Spread sauce on puff pastry
2. Add toppings like veggies, meat & herbs
3. Sprinkle cheese
4. Roll it up tight
5. Cut in to 2-3cm thick disks
6. Egg wash & pop on a non stick tray
7. Bake for 12-15 mins or until puffy & golden
8. Serve hot or cold

For the twists: cut your topped pastry in to 3-4cm wide strips & twist!

You can TAP to shop all the fabulous Liewood tableware
